div.div: This strategy delegates the variance to the new security tool system, so any injected variance would have to be routed through the new tool, delaying hacks while malicious users learn the new system.

An improvement on this strategy might be rotating security tools applied at any given time, and automating their generation so a new version can be applied for a temporary period & then never repeated.
An example of generating a new security tool would be varying its parameters:
- subset or combination of existing components
